h2. Watir 1.5

The "new users guide":http://wiki.openqa.org/display/WTR/User+Guide provides an 
introduction to using Watir. 

View this  
"succinct summary of the Watir API":http://wiki.openqa.org/display/WTR/Methods+supported+by+Element
and the provided methods and attributes. For more detailed API documentionation, refer to Watir's _rdoc_ 
-- the standard format for documenting Ruby gems. To view the *Watir rdoc:* 
# Go to the Start menu, and select Ruby -> RubyGems -> Start RubyGems Rdoc Server. 
# Select Ruby -> RubyGems -> View Installed Gems Rdoc. 
# Select the Watir rdoc in the list that appears.

The "FAQ":http://wiki.openqa.org/display/WTR/FAQ provides answers to frequently 
asked questions.

There are also several "articles":http://wiki.openqa.org/display/WTR/Articles about Watir.

h2. Watir 1.4

The "old users guide":http://wtr.rubyforge.org/watir_user_guide.html still has 
useful information in it for Watir 1.5 users.

The "old rdoc":http://wtr.rubyforge.org/rdoc/index.html is online and easy to browse, if somewhat out of date.
